#: persons-overview.rst:1
msgid "Overview: Persons"
msgstr "Visão geral: Pessoas"

#: persons-overview.rst:4
msgid "What are persons?"
msgstr ""

#: persons-overview.rst:7
msgid "A :ref:`person`` is a human being who existed at some point in time. The Monitor structures data on persons affiliated with or holding positions (a :ref:`posting`) in any specific :ref:`unit` of security forces at a particular point in time."
msgstr ""

#: persons-overview.rst:9
msgid "Data about persons are captured in two claim types:"
msgstr ""

#: persons-overview.rst:11
msgid ":ref:`person`: this claim type records basic information about a person's identity such as their name, aliases and the country in whose security forces they serve."
msgstr ""

#: persons-overview.rst:12
msgid ":ref:`posting`: data about a person's career in the security forces, including the units to which they've been posted, their roles in those units, ranks and titles obtains."
msgstr ""

